  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable WASH interventions for Riverine, Agro-pastoral and vulnerable communities to improve access to Water, Sanitation and Hygiene in Jowhar District, Middle Shabelle region.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will give attention to dire humanitarian needs in living conditions of crisis affected communities in services in Jowhar district of Middle Shabelle Region of Hirshabelle State through sustainable access to water, hygiene and sanitation. The activities will improve current WASH gaps to reduce incidents of AWD cholera spread, morbidity and mortality among emergency affected riverine and IDP communities, vulnerable populations with high burden of active Agro-pastoral/Cholera outbreaks. WASH services of good hygiene and sanitation practices will be promoted in the affected communities by providing adequate WASH facilities such as construction of new communal latrines in the hotspots, provision of WASH packages to vulnerable affected communities, provision of clean drinking water and establishing water system, rehabilitation of Shallow wells with installation of hand pumps in vulnerable host communities, agro-pastoral and riverine communities and IDPs  with WASH package  and  Establishment of water committees for ensuring continuity of services like  (hygiene promotion, hygiene kit, household water treatment).</narrative>
  </description>
